{"title":"Izhar","link":"/en/wol/d/r1/lp-e/1200002251","html":"<span id=\"page1238\" class=\"pageNum\" data-no=\"1238\" data-before-text=\"1238\"></span><strong>IZHAR</strong>(Iz&#x2B9;har).Two names, spelled similarly in Hebrew, are rendered the same in English.<strong>1. </strong><em>Yits&#xB7;har&#x2B9;. </em>The second listed of Kohath&#x2019;s four sons; therefore a grandson of Levi. (<a href=\"/en/wol/bc/r1/lp-e/1200002251/0/0\" data-bid=\"1-1\" class=\"b\">Ex 6:16,</a><a href=\"/en/wol/bc/r1/lp-e/1200002251/0/1\" data-bid=\"1-2\" class=\"b\"> 18;</a><a href=\"/en/wol/bc/r1/lp-e/1200002251/0/2\" data-bid=\"1-3\" class=\"b\"> Nu 3:17,</a><a href=\"/en/wol/bc/r1/lp-e/1200002251/0/3\" data-bid=\"1-4\" class=\"b\"> 19;</a><a href=\"/en/wol/bc/r1/lp-e/1200002251/0/4\" data-bid=\"1-5\" class=\"b\"> 1Ch 6:2,</a><a href=\"/en/wol/bc/r1/lp-e/1200002251/0/5\" data-bid=\"1-6\" class=\"b\">&#xA0;18</a>) One of Izhar&#x2019;s three sons, Korah, was executed in the wilderness for rebellion.<wbr>&#x2014;<a href=\"/en/wol/bc/r1/lp-e/1200002251/1/0\" data-bid=\"2-1\" class=\"b\">Ex 6:21;</a><a href=\"/en/wol/bc/r1/lp-e/1200002251/1/1\" data-bid=\"2-2\" class=\"b\"> Nu 16:1,</a><a href=\"/en/wol/bc/r1/lp-e/1200002251/1/2\" data-bid=\"2-3\" class=\"b\">&#xA0;32</a>.Izhar founded the Levite family of Izharites. (<a href=\"/en/wol/bc/r1/lp-e/1200002251/2/0\" data-bid=\"3-1\" class=\"b\">Nu 3:27</a>) Under King David, some of the Izharites, whose headman was Shelomith, were appointed singers, officers, and judges, while others performed regular Levitical duties.<wbr>&#x2014;<a href=\"/en/wol/bc/r1/lp-e/1200002251/3/0\" data-bid=\"4-1\" class=\"b\">1Ch 6:31-38;</a><a href=\"/en/wol/bc/r1/lp-e/1200002251/3/1\" data-bid=\"4-2\" class=\"b\"> 23:12,</a><a href=\"/en/wol/bc/r1/lp-e/1200002251/3/2\" data-bid=\"4-3\" class=\"b\"> 18;</a><a href=\"/en/wol/bc/r1/lp-e/1200002251/3/3\" data-bid=\"4-4\" class=\"b\"> 24:20-22;</a><a href=\"/en/wol/bc/r1/lp-e/1200002251/3/4\" data-bid=\"4-5\" class=\"b\"> 26:23,</a><a href=\"/en/wol/bc/r1/lp-e/1200002251/3/5\" data-bid=\"4-6\" class=\"b\"> 29</a>; see <a class=\"it\" href=\"/en/wol/tc/r1/lp-e/1200002251/0\">AMMINADAB</a> No.&#xA0;2.<strong>2. </strong><em>Yits&#xB7;char&#x2B9; </em>(in agreement with <em>Vg</em>)<em>. </em>A descendant of Judah; a son of Ashhur and Helah. (<a href=\"/en/wol/bc/r1/lp-e/1200002251/4/0\" data-bid=\"5-1\" class=\"b\">1Ch 4:1,</a><a href=\"/en/wol/bc/r1/lp-e/1200002251/4/1\" data-bid=\"5-2\" class=\"b\"> 5,</a><a href=\"/en/wol/bc/r1/lp-e/1200002251/4/2\" data-bid=\"5-3\" class=\"b\">&#xA0;7</a>) In the margin of the Masoretic text the name is spelled Zohar."}